54	Austria	eased and prolongued seasonal migration	2002	2002 Amendment to the Aliens Act - facilitates the employment of seasonal workers by allowing up to 8.000 such laborers to work every year in areas outside agriculture and tourism  and extending the employment period to up to one year.  > The law allows temporary employment of non-EU citizens by non-seasonal industries with labour shortages for six months. This is renewable for another six months. The temporary worker is then expected to return home for at least two months before taking up a job in Austria again. There is no provision for family reunion and workers are not eligible for unemployment benefits. Critics have argued that the new regulation may initiate a new guest worker regime, with thousands of foreign workers coming into Austria for whom all legal paths to consolidate residency are closed.	MPI 2003	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Low-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
