57	Austria	introduced compulsory integration courses	2002	Integration Agreement Decree of 2002  (Integrationsvereinbarung) - requiring all new immigrants from non-EU third countries (plus those who have been living in Austria since 1998) to sign an Integration Agreement and to attend 'integration courses' consisting mainly of language instruction (100 hours) and an introduction to fundamental legal, historical, and political aspects of Austria.  > This Agreement is compulsory for all third country nationals, who settled down in Austria after 1 January 1998, or who are granted a first settlement permit after 1 January 2003. The obligations have to be fulfilled by the alien within a period of four years. Non-participation will lead to sanctions, both financial and legal, e.g., the denial of more secure residence titles. The ultimate fate of non-compliant foreigners could be expulsion from Austria.	MPI 2003; EMN 2005: 31	Major change	National policy	Integration	Language, housing and cultural integration programmes	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
