76	Austria	integration and language requirements expanded for residents	2006	Settlement and Residence Act 2005 -  expanded the scale and scope of the integration courses for immigrants by augmenting the obligatory german course from 100 to 300 hours > The requirement concerns all third country nationals (thus exempting EEC- and Swiss nationals), newcomers as well as persons who wanted to renew their residence title. They have to comply with this agreement that consists of two modules, the first one focussing on alphabetization (reading and writing) and the second one on the German language with the goal to be able to participate in the social, economic and cultural life of Austria. In case of not taking part or not passing these courses within five years, immigrants are threatened with sanctions such as exclusion from more secure residence titles or even the loss of the residence permit, which means expulsion from Austria.	SOPEMI 2007: 232	Minor change	National policy	Integration	Language, housing and cultural integration programmes	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
