250	Belgium	resolutions to improve integration adopted	1995	Resolutions were adopted by the Inter-ministerial Conference in September 1995 to facilitate the integration of foreigners.  > The main focus was to concentrate human and financial resources on specific projects in large urban areas. It was decided to implement legislation without delay to make naturalisation procedures faster and more flexible.	SOPEMI 2006: 80, 81	N/A	N/A	Integration	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
251	Belgium	displaced person status was abolished	1995	In March 1995, the displaced person status, created in 1992 to handle requests for asylum from nationals of former Yugoslavia, was abolished.  > Thus, all displaced persons from this region (not including nationals of Bosnia-Herzegovina, Kosovo and certain regions of Croatia) will be required to leave Belgium and displaced person status will no longer be granted to new immigrants from these regions. It is likely that a number of these persons, not wishing to return to their country of origin, have duly applied for asylum and have stayed in Belgium illegally.	SOPEMI 2006: 80	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	Specific nationalities	Former Yugoslavia	More restrictive		
252	Belgium	Schengen agreement implemented by BE	1995	Schengen Agreement signed in 1985, implemented in 1995 - The Schengen agreements removes all border controls while attempting to strengthen the common external frontier.	Ortega and Peri 2009	Major change	Multi- or bilateral policy	Border and land control	Free mobility rights/agreements	All	EU citizens	EU member states at that time	Less restrictive		
253	Belgium	Integration measures in the French regions	1996	Decree of 4 July 1996 concerning the integration of foreign nationals - is the framework for the integration policy in the French regions and established six regional centres for the integration of foreign nationals or people of foreign origin in the French-speaking area to provide for the development of integration activities on the social, socio-economic, cultural and educational levels, in the area of accommodation and health, preferably in the framework of agreements concluded with the local authorities and associations.	EMN 2004: 20	N/A	N/A	Integration	Language, housing and cultural integration programmes	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
254	Belgium	stricter asylum procedure	1996	Law of 10 and 15 July 1996 tightens the Act of 15 December 1980 in order to limit the entry and settlement of nationals from non-European Union countries - bringing the law on asylum procedure into line with the commitments made under the Schengen Agreement: all applicants for asylum will now be accommodated in a reception centre and will no longer be free to choose the language in which their case is dealt with	SOPEMI 2006: 80	Major change	National policy	Border and land control	Institutional capacities	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
255	Belgium	family member can be required to leave in certain circumstances	1996	Law of 10 and 15 July 1996 tightens the Act of 15 December 1980 in order to limit the entry and settlement of nationals from non-European Union countries - making it possible that family members may receive orders to leave the territory if their income and living conditions are not satisfactory	SOPEMI 2006: 80	Major change	National policy	Exit	Expulsion	Family members	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
256	Belgium	detention period for irregular migrants extended	1996	Law of 10 and 15 July 1996 tightens the Act of 15 December 1980 in order to limit the entry and settlement of nationals from non-European Union countries - extending the period of detention of a foreigner in an illegal situation from 2 to 8 months. During this period, the relevant authorities are responsible for making the necessary arrangements for return to the home country.	SOPEMI 2006: 80; Carlier and Rea 2001: 14	Minor change	National policy	Border and land control	Detention	Irregular migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
257	Belgium	more carrier responsibilities	1996	Law of 10 and 15 July 1996 tightens the Act of 15 December 1980 in order to limit the entry and settlement of nationals from non-European Union countries - placing greater responsibility on transport operators, conferring on them the duty to check not only the entry papers required from the foreigners but also that passengers have the means to support themselves during their stay in Belgium.	SOPEMI 2006: 80	Minor change	National policy	Border and land control	Carrier liabilities	All	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
258	Belgium	students required to prove funding	1996	Law of 10 and 15 July 1996 tightens the Act of 15 December 1980 in order to limit the entry and settlement of nationals from non-European Union countries - requiring foreign students to prove that they have sufficient funds to live on their own and any person prolonging their studies excessively can be refused permission to stay.	SOPEMI 2006: 80	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	International students	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
