263	Belgium	committee on forced repatriation practices	1999	In 1999, as a consequence of the death in 1998 of an refused Nigerian female asylum seeker during attempted repatriation, a Committee was established on the instructions of the Government (the so-called Vermeersch Committee) - to assess the expulsion of asylum seekers whose legal remedies had been exhausted.  > The Committee then gave an opinion about the various phases of the removal, including the admissible means of coercion. The latter may not compromise the health or security of the refugees being expelled. The recommendations made by the Committee were transformed into best practices for removal.	EMN 2004: 8	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Exit	Institutional capacities	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
