284	Belgium	communal voting rights granted to all foreigners after 5 years	2004	Law of 19 March 2004 - grants the right to vote in municipal elections to non EU foreigners who have resided in Belgium for at least 5 years. It will be in force for the first time for the 2006 elections. > However, three limitations were set to this right: they acquire the right to vote but not to be elected; they must register in the voting register and when registering must sign a declaration committing themselves to observe the Constitution, the laws of the land and the European Convention of Human Rights.	Ortega and Peri 2009; SOPEMI 2006: 168; EMN 2004: 13	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to justice and political rights	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
