288	Belgium	More protection from expulsion for long term residents and other categories	2005	Law of 26 May 2005 - reformed the double punishment, the common name for the detention of foreign nationals who have committed a serious criminal offence and their expulsion from the territory after the end of their prison term > Now, a foreign national who was born in Belgium or arrived before the age of 12 and has principally and regularly resided here ever since and a recognised refugee may not in any case be sent back or expelled. Other categories of foreign nationals who have lived in Belgium for several years or have ties here now enjoy greater protection from being expelled or sent back.	EMN 2005: 28	Mid-level change	National policy	Exit	Expulsion	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
