306	Belgium	marriages with foreigners under more control for three years	2008	Law of 25 April 2007 modifying the Aliens Act created new means for combating marriage abuses came into force on 01.06.2008 - stipulated that up to three years after married partners received the right to stay in Belgium, the residence permit can be retrieved if one does not comply anymore with the residence conditions stipulated in the Aliens Act.  > In the two first years after the reunification or family formation, the fact that both partners do not live physically together anymore is sufficient to retrieve the residence permit. In the course of the third year, a negative opinion of the Public Prosecutor with regard to the marriage is sufficient to end the right of stay. After three years, a judicial instance has to rule the annulment of the marriage before the residence permit can be retrieved.	EMN 2008: 13	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Family members	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
307	Belgium	new unit to facilitate Economic migration	2008	In September 2008, a new unit Economic Migration was created within the Immigration Department - showing that facilitating access of foreign (high-skilled) workers to the Belgian labour market through the already existing but complicated procedures is effectively a priority  > The government recognises the possibility of economic migration from third countries to fill labour market shortages. A service for economic migrants has been set up within the Foreign Nationals Office, whose main objective is to expedite visas and residence permits for business or work reasons	EMN 2008: 5; SOPEMI 2009	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Institutional capacities	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
