326	Belgium	introduction of safe country of origin list	2012	Royal Decree on 1 June 2012 - introduced the concept of safe countries of origin  > On 11 May 2012, the government decided to put the following countries on such a list: Albania, Bosnia-Herzegovina, Montenegro, FYROM, Kosovo, Serbia and India. The list will be revised at least once a year. The asylum procedure for applicants from these countries is shortened: the CGRS has to take a decision within 15 working days and the burden of proof is higher. The appeal possibilities are limited to an annulment procedure, which has no automatic suspensive effect.	EMN 2012: 6, 33	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	Specific nationalities	Those on the safe country of origin list (revised at least yearly)	More restrictive		
