364	Belgium	Local Integration measures in Brussels	2014	Local Integration measures in Brussels (decree on the reception and integration pathways for newcomers in the Brussels Capital Region was approved on 18th July 2013), Wallonia (Decree on the integration pathway for newcomers in the Walloon region was approved on 27th February 2014) or Flanders (structural reform with the establishment of the External Autonomous (Civic) Integration Agency)		Fine-tuning change	National policy	Integration	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
365	Belgium	Institutional change	2014	March 2014 the former Centre for Equal Opportunities and Opposition to Racism has been converted and transformed into two institutions:   - Federal migration Centre  - The Interfederal Centre for Equal Opportunities   The tasks of the Interfederal Centre for Equal Opportunities have been expanded to include competence for the regions and the communities, in addition to its authority at the federal level. This is an important step in the fight against discrimination and racism because it enables every resident to approach one and the same institution for any request on information, advice or assistance on the subject of discrimination (with the exception of sex discrimination), without having to wonder whether this is a federal, regional or community matter. Due to the fact that all expertise is pooled, citizens will also be certain to receive the best possible treatment.	EMN  p.7	N/A	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Institutional capacities	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
366	Belgium	system of National Rapporteur or Equivalent, human trafficking	2014	1st of September 2014 a Royal Decree of 21th of July 2014: Belgium has established its system of National Rapporteur or Equivalent mechanism in a specific way: it is composed, on the one hand, of the Interdepartmental coordination unit, as coordination mechanism and state rapporteur, and on the other hand, of the Federal Migration Centre as independent rapporteur. The decree also formally integrated the specialized reception centres for victims of THB in the Interdepartmental Coordination Unit. Before, the specialized reception centres regularly attended certain meetings of the Bureau of the platform, but they were not official members of the platform.	EMN	N/A	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Institutional capacities	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
