372	Belgium	The Royal Decree of 13 February 2015, residence permit	2015	The Royal Decree of 13 February 2015 on this issue was published in the Belgian Official Gazette. The long term resident status is now also open to foreigners who do not yet have a residence permit of unlimited duration.  However a number of categories of foreigners with a permit of limited duration are still excluded from the status (those with student residence permit; au pairs, seasonal workers, posted workers; persons with a diplomatic, consular or special identity card; ).  Other modifications include:    - the fact that a legal and uninterrupted stay of 5 years is necessary to receive the status (including certain periods of temporary residence rights)  - the fact that the Immigration Office needs to do a test of proportionality in certain cases when taking a negative decision on the basis of national security or public order.	EMN p.22 report 2014	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Access to permanent residence	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
