411	Belgium	The law of 24 February 2017 and the law of 15 March 2017, return and expulsion	2017	The law of 24 February 2017 and the law of 15 March 2017 (modifying the law of 15 december 1980 on the entry, residence, settlement and removal or foreign nationals in order to reinforce the protection of public order and national security): Residence of certain categories of thirdcountry nationals (e.g. longterm residents) can be ended for serious reasons of public order or national security. Decisions to end the residence of a thirdcountry national must be based on the individual behaviour of the concerned person and cannot be justified on economic grounds. The behaviour of the concerned person must represent a genuine, real and serious enough threat to society. The length of the third country national's stay in Belgium, his/her ties with the country of residence and the consequences of the removal to his/her family life must be taken into account during the decision making.	EMN	Mid-level change	National policy	Exit	Entry visa/stay permit	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
412	Belgium	The law of 24 February 2017 and the law of 15 March 2017, return and expulsion	2017	Changes were also introduced regarding the procedure for issuing removal orders. When someone subject to a removal order is granted a temporary residence permit, the removal order is no longer withdrawn but only temporarily suspended during the period covered by the temporary residence permit. If the application for residence or international protection is rejected, the suspension of the removal order is lifted. The possibility to appeal against the removal order is only possible one time. Therefore, once the suspension of the removal order is lifted, it is often no longer possible to appeal against it (as the delay for appeal has lapsed since then). A new removal order will be only issued if new elements are available to justify the removal.	EMN	Mid-level change	National policy	Exit	Expulsion	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
