969	Cyprus	Change in the policy regarding the detention of asylum seekers	2014	Change in the policy regarding the detention of asylum seekers  introduced a fast track examination of asylum applications of detained asylum seekers  the Asylum Service will interview and reach a decision on the application within 30 days; If protection is granted the detainee will be released .If the application is rejected and the applicant submits an appeal to the Reviewing Authority, then the Refugee Reviewing Authority will issue a decision within 15 days. If protection is granted the detainee will be released. In the event that due to the complexity of a case, a decision cannot be reached within 30 days, then the detainee will be released.	AIDA update 2015 p.62	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Detention	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
