1125	Czech Republic	definition of czech citizens and transitional provisions	1993	Act No. 40/1993 on the Acquisition and Loss of Czech Citizenship - set transitory provisions regulating the initial determination of the citizens of the new state: natural persons, who were citizens of the Czech Republic as of 31 December 1992, are citizens of the Czech Republic as of 1 January 1993.  > The Slovak legislators adopted the same approach as regards overall (collective) initial determination. This prevented de iure statelessness in the wake of the break-up of Czechoslovakia.	Barsova 2013: 5	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	All	Citizens	N/A	Less restrictive		
1126	Czech Republic	ius sanguinis enshrined in law	1993	Act No. 40/1993 on the Acquisition and Loss of Czech Citizenship - based the acquisition of citizenship on the ius sanguinis principle: A child might acquire Czech citizenship only if at least one of his parents is a Czech citizen.	Drbohlav et al 2009: 55	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	All	All	N/A	Less restrictive		
1127	Czech Republic	naturalisation requirements set	1993	Act No. 40/1993 on the Acquisition and Loss of Czech Citizenship - established rules for the naturalisation of immigrants: Applicants have to stay in the Czech Republic on a permanent residence permit for at least 5 years and during that time usually reside in the country.  > Also, they have to give up the former citizenship, except in specific cases such as asylum. Thus, officially dual citizenship is not permitted, however, in many cases it can be allowed for. The applicant must further prove that he/she has not been lawfully convicted of a premeditated criminal offence during the last 5 years and has to fulfil obligations related to health and social insurance, taxes etc. Finally, his/her knowledge of the Czech language has to be proven. No standardised tests have been set yet; applicants only go through a simple interview at a local municipality office.	Drbohlav et al 2009: 55	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
1128	Czech Republic	preferential naturalisation procedure for slovaks	1993	Act No. 40/1993 on the Acquisition and Loss of Czech Citizenship - created a simplified mechanism for Slovak citizens, enabling them to acquire Czech citizenship after permanent residence in the Czech Republic for at least 2 years, abandonment of Slovak citizenship and no lawful conviction of a premeditated criminal offence during the last 5 years. > The application deadline for this option procedure was at first set by the end of 1993, later extended to mid-1994.	Drbohlav et al 2009: 55	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	All migrants	Specific nationalities	Slovak Republic	Less restrictive		
1129	Czech Republic	Readmission agreement with Austria, Vietnam, Slovak Republic, Poland and Romania	1993	Czech Republic signed a readmission bilateral agreement with Austria, Vietnam, Slovak Republic, Poland and Romania	SOPEMI 1995: 141; SOPEMI 1997: 91	Mid-level change	Multi- or bilateral policy	Exit	Readmission agreements	Irregular migrants	All foreign nationalities	Those transiting through or originating from Austria, Vietnam, Slovak Republic, Poland or Romania	More restrictive		
1130	Czech Republic	visa free agreements with European countries, other arrangement with eastern countries	1993	Visa-free agreements have been signed with most European countries.  > Citizens of Turkey, Cyprus, Albania, Andorra, former Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro), Bosnia-Herzegovina, Armenia, Azerbaijan and Georgia, however, need an entry visa. Nationals from Romania, Russia, the Ukraine, the Baltic States, Bulgaria and Moldova are required to show an official letter of invitation from a Czech national or institution, from a foreign permanent resident or a voucher from a travel agency.	SOPEMI 1995: 141	N/A	Multi- or bilateral policy	Legal entry and stay	Travel visa/permit	All	Specific nationalities	European countries	N/A		
