1163	Czech Republic	end of epatriation programme for czech descendants	2001	In mid-2001, the state program for the immigration of Czech compatriots (descendants)  was officially terminated  > Altogether 818 persons from Kazakhstan, Russia, Uzbekistan, Kyrgyzstan, and Moldova immigrated to the Czech Republic. Since then, immigrants with Czech origins have had to use a standard immigration procedure with no special state support.	Drbohlav et al 2009: 49	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Reintegration/return programmes	Diaspora	Specific nationalities	Kazakhstan, Russia, Uzbekistan, Kyrgyzstan, Moldova	More restrictive		
