1474	Denmark	Amendment of the rules on Family Reunification	2016	Amendment of the rules on Family Reunification  the attachment requirement will now be applied to everyone. The attachment requirement calls on married couples to prove that they have stronger united ties to Denmark than to any other country, which means that roughly 200,000 expatriate Danes will be generally cut off from family reunification because they have been gone from Denmark for so long that they now have a stronger connection to another country. Before, couples could still qualify for family reunification if one of them had been a Danish citizen for at least 26 years.	https://www.thelocal.dk/20160629/denmark-makes-it-harder-for-foreign-spouses-to-come/	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Diaspora	Citizens	Danish	More restrictive		
