1733	Finland	EU 2004 enlargement transitional restrictions	2004	EU 2004 Enlargement - Finland did not directly grant labout market access to the EU8, but imposed transitional arrangements where a work permit would be granted only where a Finnish national cannot be found for the job.  > This did however not apply to students, part-time workers, entrepreneurs, people living in Finland for non-work purposes, people who were already living in Finland for a year or people who would be entitled to work anyway if they were from a third country.	http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/3513889.stm#finland [accessed on 11.09.2013]	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	All migrant workers	EU citizens	Czech Republic, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland, Slovakia and Slovenia	No change		
