1735	Finland	asylum procedure laid down	2004	A new Aliens Act entered into force in May 2004 -governing the asylum procedure and the competencies of asylum institutions. The Act provides grounds for granting international protection as well as other, non-protection related grounds for a residence permit, which must be considered during a single asylum procedure.  >  The requirements for granting asylum under the Aliens Act are identical to those in the 1951 Convention.	EMN 2009: 9	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
1736	Finland	family reunification criteria set	2004	A new Aliens Act entered into force in May 2004 -setting certain prerequisites for a residence permit on the grounds of family ties: Applicants must submit a statement of there being a family tie with a person residing in Finland and an intention of leading a family life in the country. In addition, the applicant must prove that he/she is capable of securing his/her means of support without becoming dependent on social assistance or other similar benefit.	EMN 2012: 137	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Family members	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
