1738	Finland	Action plan against THB	2005	In August 2005, the government adopted an action plan against human trafficking - which specifies the measures against human trafficking to be implemented in the various sectors of the administration. > Background: Human trafficking was not considered an actual problem in Finland - and cases confirmed by court sentences are still rare - until accusations by the United States forced the Finnish government to allocate resources for researching it.	SOPEMI 2007: 244; Leitzinger 2010: 142	N/A	N/A	Border and land control	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
1739	Finland	Migration Policy Programme adopted	2006	The Finnish government adopted a Migration Policy Programme in October 2006 - The main emphasis of the programme is on the promotion of labour migration. In this context, the entry of foreign graduates from Finnish universities into the Finnish labour market will be facilitated by a series of measures, including teaching in Finnish and Swedish, training placements and an expansion of the residence permit for job search to ten months. Other central themes include the promotion of integration, a more flexible allocation of the refugee quota, changes in the selection of quota refugees and a simplification of the permit system. The special regime for the immigration of Ingrians (ethnic Finns, mainly from Russia) will be phased out.	SOPEMI 2007: 244; EMN 2008: 7	N/A	N/A	Legal entry and stay	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
