1757	Finland	action plan against illegal entry	2009	Action plan against illegal entry into the country for 2010-2011 - to suggest measures to fight illegal immigration. The measures were set to cover four levels of operation according to the border security model of the EU's unified border security system: countries of origin and transit, neighbouring and nearby countries, the external borders and within the country.  > The action plan focuses particularly on the monitoring of foreigners within the country. In order to ensure broad social acceptance, the working group's report was widely circulated for comment. The plan includes key proposals for measures to be implemented, particularly concerning the shar-ing and use of information. Proposals pertaining to legislative amendments have been prepared with a conservative approach and the human rights perspective is the starting point for all operations.	EMN 2010: 46	N/A	N/A	Border and land control	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	Irregular migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
