2090	France	The decree of 17 April 2015 introduces a new mechanism for assisted return and reintegration	2015	The decree of 17 April 2015 introduces a new mechanism for assisted return and reintegration that aims to encourage voluntary return among third country nationals by differentiating different amounts according to the area of origin. The mechanism thus aims at three categories:  - Third country nationals subject to a visa: the allocation is increased from 500 to 650 per person, with a view to making it more incentivizing - Nationals of third countries who are exempt from visas and Kosovo citizens: the amount of assistance is reduced from 500 to 300 per person, to avoid windfall effects - EU nationals: the amount of assistance is unchanged, at 50 per person.	EMN p. 39	Mid-level change	National policy	Exit	Reintegration/return programmes	Irregular migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
