2101	France	« passeport talent - carte bleue européenne - exercice d'une activité salariée ».	2016	The talent passport (passeport talent): The « passeport talent - carte bleue européenne - exercice d'une activité salariée ». Applicants must hold a qualification demonstrating at least three years of higher education have at least five years of comparable professional experience, a one year work contract and a gross salary of 53.836 minimum a year.	https://blog.parisattitude.com/en/french-passeport-talent  - https://www.hg.org/legal-articles/how-to-get-french-tech-visa-and-talent-passport-49476	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
2102	France	The passeport talent - création d'entreprise	2016	The talent passport (passeport talent): The passeport talent - création d'entreprise: The applicants must have a real and serious business project in France. However, exceptionally, an acquisition of a stake (which means taking control of a business) may be regarded as a business creation project depending on the nature and characteristics of the project. The company can be commercial, artisanal (handcraft work) or industrial. The applicant must invest at least 30,000 in the project and must hold  a degree at least equivalent to a master's degree or be able to prove at least five years of professional experience at a comparable level.	https://blog.parisattitude.com/en/french-passeport-talent  https://www.hg.org/legal-articles/how-to-get-french-tech-visa-and-talent-passport-49476	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Investors, entrepreneurs and business people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
2103	France	The passeport talent - projet économique innovant:	2016	The passeport talent - projet économique innovant: Applicants have to apply with an innovative economical project which has been recognized as such by a French public agency. Applicants must show documents establishing its innovative nature, object and/or duration as well as the document proving it has been recognized by a public body. Applicants must prove that they are earning at least the minimum French wage (called SMIC in France and equivalent of a gross 1.500 a month)	https://blog.parisattitude.com/en/french-passeport-talent  https://www.hg.org/legal-articles/how-to-get-french-tech-visa-and-talent-passport-49476	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Investors, entrepreneurs and business people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
