2327	Germany	ad hoc resettlement programme for syrians	2013	In March 2013, Germany agreed to grant humanitarian admission to 5,000 Syrian refugees. >  The programme grants those arriving, a temporary residence status, with the expectation that refugees will return to Syria when the conflict there has been resolved.	http://www.resettlement.eu//country/germany [accessed on 30.09.2013]	Mid-level change	Multi- or bilateral policy	Legal entry and stay	Resettlement programmes	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	Specific nationalities	Syria	Less restrictive		
2328	Germany	reduced waiting period for the labour market access of asylum-seekers to nine months.	2013	Amendments to the Asylum Procedure Act (version of 6 September 2013) , in view of the recast Reception Conditions Directive (2013/33/EU) - reduced the waiting period for the labour market access of asylum-seekers to nine months.	EMN 2013: 2	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
2329	Germany	easing of work permit for certain occupation groups and university graduates	2013	Employment Ordinance (Beschäftigungsverordnung) of July 2013 - employers may now recruit third country nationals who have completed their vocational training abroad in certain occupation groups with a lack of qualified personnel in Germany. The labour market test by the Federal Employment Agency has been completely waived for university graduates in many cases.	SOPEMI 2014: 256	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
