2386	Germany	Return	2015	The Act on the redefinition of the right to stay and the termination of residence, which came into effect on 1 August 2015, amends the provisions concerning expulsions set out in sections 5356 of the Residence Act. The three-tier expulsion system was replaced by a provision which requires the foreigners authorities to find a balance between the foreigners interest in staying in Germany and the states interest in expelling him or her in the individual case. Until 1 August 2015, the law distinguished between mandatory expulsion, regular expulsion and discretionary expulsion, which permitted or obliged the authorities to respond to threats to public order and safety.	https://ec.europa.eu/home-affairs/sites/homeaffairs/files/11a_germany_return_study_en.pdf	Mid-level change	National policy	Exit	Expulsion	Irregular migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
