2403	Germany	Ordinance accompanying the Integration Act implemented the Fourth Ordinance to Amend the Employment Regulation	2016	Ordinance accompanying the Integration Act implemented the Fourth Ordinance to Amend the Employment Regulation - the priority check will be suspended in 133 out of 156 districts of the Federal Employment Agency in the case of asylum applicants and persons whose deportation has been suspended. The suspension period will be three years (BMAS 2016b). As a result, asylum seekers and persons whose deportation has been suspended will get easier access to the labour market after three months.	EMN ?	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
