2432	Germany	Act to Fight Child Marriage entered into force on 22 July 2017	2017	Act to Fight Child Marriage entered into force on 22 July 2017. - It stipulates that all marriages, including those entered into in third countries, are in principle invalid as long as one of the spouses is under 18 years old at the date of the wedding. The definition of 'unaccompanied' minors in Section 42a (1) of the Social Code Book VIII, now also takes into account married minors if they arrive in Germany without a parent or another person with the right of custody.	EMN?	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Family members	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
