2450	Germany	model project for a central service point for foreign skilled workers	2019	As part of the Skilled Workers immigration act of March 2020, but already entering into force in August 2019 - Launch of a model project to triall a central servicepoint for the recognition of foreign skilled workers, which should advice foreigners about the possibilities of accreditation of foreign qualifications and visa procedures. The project runs until december 2023.	https://www.asyl.net/view/detail/News/weitere-gesetze-aus-dem-migrationspaket-im-bundesgesetzblatt-veroeffentlicht/ [accessed on 21.02.2021]	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Institutional capacities	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
