2476	Germany	skilled workers with recognised qualifications able to come to Germany for up to 6 months to seek employment or further training	2020	Skilled Workers Immigration Act of March 2020 - As already possible for university graduates, skilled workers with recognised vocational qualifications will be able to come to Germany for up to six months to seek employment. They have to be able to finance their stay and provide proof of at least intermediate German language skills. Changes also allow those whose foreign qualifications that are only partially recognised to come to Germany to seek a training position (Ausbildungsplatz) if they are below 25 years old.	SOPEMI 2020: 194; https://www.asyl.net/view/detail/News/weitere-gesetze-aus-dem-migrationspaket-im-bundesgesetzblatt-veroeffentlicht/ [accessed on 21.02.2021]	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
