2480	Greece	integration programme for pontic greeks	1990	The National Foundation for the  Reception and Resettlement of Repatriate Greeks (EYIAPOE) was established in 1990 - to manage the conditions of entrance, residence and work of Pontic Greek returnees.  > Accommodation, food, education for children and adults, and specialized courses of Greek language and professional training have been provided within the context of the Institutes programme, aiming at a successful integration of Pontic Greeks into Greek society.	Triandafyllidou and Veikou 2002: 199	Mid-level change	National policy	Integration	Language, housing and cultural integration programmes	Diaspora	All foreign nationalities	Greek Pontians	Less restrictive		
2481	Greece	eased residence permit for albanian greeks	1991	Act No 1975/1991 regulating the admission of aliens (replaced by Act 2910/2001) - provides Greek Albanians with a preferential legal status; allowing them to register at the Aliens Department of the Greek Ministry of the Interior and Public Order and get a Temporary Residence Permit more easily than other immigrants.  > Because of their ethnic minority status in southern Albania, they are perceived as refugees who suffered persecution and discrimination because of their Greek nationality and Christian Orthodox religion.	Triandafyllidou and Veikou 2002: 199	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Diaspora	Specific nationalities	Ethnic Greeks from Albania	Less restrictive		
