2483	Greece	labour market test and other criteria for workers introduced	1991	Act No 1975/1991 regulating the admission of aliens (replaced by Act 2910/2001) - established strict rules for recruitment of foreign workers: a foreign worker was depended on his/her employer and in case of his/her dismissal, the migrant has to be deported. > The Ministries of Employment, Foreign Policy and Public Order were responsible for issuing the work permits according to the needs of the labour market in each region. Priority is given to those of Greek origin, EC citizens and refugees recognised by government in order to fill a vacancy.	Triandafyllidou and Veikou 2002: 196	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	All migrant workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
2484	Greece	stricter requirements for asylum	1991	Act No 1975/1991 regulating the admission of aliens (replaced by Act 2910/2001) - restricts the conditions for recognition of refugee status.  >  Immediately after arrival and not in the transit area, someone should apply for asylum seeker status. The reason for valid application is fear of persecution. The right to appeal for applicant is within 2 days and the police authorities have to take the decisionwithin 5 days. It grands some rights to refugees and provides the issue of a series of inter-ministrial and presentatial Decrees which cover employment and social assistance for asylum seekers and refugees.  This law was amended by the law  2452/1996.	Triandafyllidou and Veikou 2002: 196	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
