2524	Greece	family members get direct access to labour market	2001	Act 2910/2001 on the entry, residence and naturalisation of immigrants in Greece (entered into force on 2 June 2001; amended by Act 3013/2002) - gives direct labour market access to the aliens' family members > Despite governmental claims that it constituted a big leap towards modernisation, law 2910/2001 was severely criticized for not taken into account human rights considerations. As a consequence, the three year restriction for the access to the aliens family members to the labour market in the bill was finally dropped from the law.	Zigoura 2007: 24	Major change	National policy	Integration	Work visa/permit	Family members	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
