2559	Greece	regularisation of irregular migrants facilitated	2007	Law 3536/2007 amended the 2005 immigration bill - widened the access to the 2005 regularisation programme.  > Additional documents, such as birth certificates of children born in Greece, are now accepted. In addition, migrants who are unable to provide proof of the full number of 200 or 150 days employed were given the opportunity to buy up to 20% of the required number of days by a payment into the social security system. For a range of occupations, the required number of days has been halved. Finally, third country nationals who attended public primary or secondary schools or universities may now also benefit from the regularisation and the regularization fee for children between the age of 14 and 18 was abolished.	SOPEMI 2007: 250	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Regularisation	Irregular migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
