2606	Greece	new Immigration Code was approved in Greece (Law 4251/2014).	2014	new Immigration Code was approved in Greece (Law 4251/2014). The Code sets out the conditions regulating legal migration, determining the maximum number of positions for dependent work, seasonal employment, the transfer of fisheries workers and highly-qualified employment. It transposed the EU Blue Card Directive which establishes a favourable framework for granting an EU Blue Card for the purpose of highly skilled employment, particularly as regards family reunification, without requiring prior two-year stay of the Blue Card holder, on condition that s/he has sufficient resources, according to the general provisions on family reunification.  The Code does not set a deadline for the EU Blue Card Holders family members access to the labour market.   It also allows for the cumulative calculation of periods of stay in different Member States to fulfil the condition relating to the duration of stay for long-term residents.   A holder of an EU Blue Card from another Member State may more easily be transferred to Greece.	EMN report	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive	check	
