2667	Greece	Appeals	2016	Law 4399/2016 amends Article 5(3) of the New Asylum Law (4375/2016)  modified the composition of the three-member Appeals Committees and removed the possibility for asylum seekers to request a personal hearing before the Committees. The term of the Committee members is three years, instead of the previously foreseen five-year term.  This legislative amendment comes shortly after several Appeals Committees decisions rebutting the safe third country presumption regarding Turkey. According to a European Commission report, as many as 70 rulings of the Appeals Committees have rebutted this presumption and overturned the related first instance decisions of the Asylum Service, while 2 have upheld the first instance inadmissibility decisions.	https://www.ecre.org/greece-amends-its-asylum-law-after-multiple-appeals-board-decisions-overturn-the-presumption-of-turkey-as-a-safe-third-country/	Minor change	National policy	legal entry and stay	Access to justice and political rights	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
