2792	Hungary	preferential treatment of ethnic hungarians on entry and work permits	2001	The Act on benefits for Ethnic Hungarians living in Neighbouring States of Hungary (Status Law) was adopted in 2001 - introducing a specific certificate for ethnic Hungarians living in Slovakia, Romania, Ukraine, Slovenia, Serbia-Montenegro and Croatia. > It entitled ethnic Hungarians in neighbouring countries to seasonal working permits and simpler procedures to obtain the right to enter, work or study in Hungary. Background: More than three million ethnic Hungarians living in neighbouring countries (e.g., Romania, the Slovak Republic, the Former Yugoslavia, the Ukraine and Croatia) have the potential of being affected by the accession of Hungary to the EU.	SOPEMI 2003a: 193; Kovacs and Toth 2013: 13; Hárs 2003	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Diaspora	Specific nationalities	Ethnic Hungarians in Slovakia, Romania, Ukraine, Slovenia, Serbia-Montenegro and Croatia.	Less restrictive		
2793	Hungary	preferential treatment of ethnic hungarians through social benefits	2001	The Act on benefits for Ethnic Hungarians living in Neighbouring States of Hungary (Status Law) was adopted in 2001 - introducing a specific certificate for ethnic Hungarians living in Slovakia, Romania, Ukraine, Slovenia, Serbia-Montenegro and Croatia. > It entitled beneficiaries to a set of cultural and economic rights, such as special benefits in education, employment, travel and culture.  Background: More than three million ethnic Hungarians living in neighbouring countries (e.g., Romania, the Slovak Republic, the Former Yugoslavia, the Ukraine and Croatia) have the potential of being affected by the accession of Hungary to the EU.	SOPEMI 2003a: 193; Kovacs and Toth 2013: 13	Mid-level change	National policy	Integration	Access to social benefits and socio-economic rights	Diaspora	Specific nationalities	Ethnic Hungarians in Slovakia, Romania, Ukraine, Slovenia, Serbia-Montenegro and Croatia.	Less restrictive		
