2804	Hungary	deportation not possible anymore when asylum application fully processed	2004	April 2004 amendments to the asylum law - revokes the possibility of implementing a deportation procedure once an application has been fully processed	SOPEMI 2005: 205	Major change	National policy	Exit	Expulsion	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
2805	Hungary	regularisation with strict conditions	2004	April 2004 amendments to the asylum law -  provides for the regularisation of certain foreigners illegally resident in Hungary who can provide proof of entry into the country prior to 1 May 2003. > Highly restrictive conditions apply to foreigners seeking regularisation under this law. They must: i) be married to a Hungarian national, or to a foreigner residing legally in Hungary or have a child of Hungarian nationality; or ii) be able to prove that they receive income as the head or manager of a company; or iii) be able to show that they have cultural links with Hungary. Applicants meeting one of these conditions may be granted a one-year residence permit. No leave is given to appeal in the event of a failed application. So far there has only been one regularisation that took place in 2004 before the EU accession of Hungary.	SOPEMI 2005: 205	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Regularisation	Irregular migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
2806	Hungary	new regulations for seasonal work	2004	New regulations regarding seasonal employment of foreigners in agriculture took effect in spring 2004 - Work permits can be granted for up to 150 days in a 12 month period. Applications may be refused if the employer is unable to respect the working conditions required or pays a wage considerably below the national average.	SOPEMI 2006: 186	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Low-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
2807	Hungary	spouses of HU nationals can work without permit	2004	Decree 21/2004 to amend the Decree No. 8/1999 on the authorization for the employment of foreign workers - allows the spouse of a Hungarian national, if the couple is living together in Hungary, is to work without a work permit	http://www.ilo.org/dyn/natlex/natlex_browse.details?p_lang=en&p_isn=72181 [accessed on 24.01.2014]	Mid-level change	National policy	Integration	Work visa/permit	Family members	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
