2835	Hungary	employers have to check legal status of workers	2011	2011 Amendment of Act II of 2007 - implemented the Employer Sanctions Directive  > Employers shall be required to ascertain before the employment of a third-country national that the third-country national affected has the permit prescribed in third-country national policing act for engaging in gainful employment. Any employer who fails to satisfy this obligation shall be subject to a penalty  specified under specific other legislation  for the protection of public policy. The employer shall keep the copy of the presented permit for the duration of employment. The employer shall be discharged from the obligation to pay fine if he/she proves that he/she had complied with monitoring and notification.	EMN 2011: 13, 51	Minor change	National policy	Border and land control	Employer liabilities	All migrant workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
2836	Hungary	EU Blue card introduced	2011	Hungary implemented the EU Blue Card Directive from August 2011 onwards - granting tertiary-educated non-EEA nationals who enter Hungary for the purposes of highly qualified employment a special permit, if their salary exceeds 1.5 times the average wage, or 1.2 times the average wage in case of shortage professions. > The threshold wage is about HUF 300 000 (EUR 1040) monthly. The EU Blue Card is valid to minimum one and maximum four years that may be extended to further four years maximally.	SOPEMI 2013: 258; EMN 2011: 12	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
