2868	Hungary	UAM	2014	Amendment of the Child Protection Act  the legal status of unaccompanied minors has been redefined, qualifying them primarily as children and thus only secondarily as migrants.  This means that the a child protection guardian employed by the Child Protection Services in charge of the guardianship of children without parental care in general have taken over the guardianship of unaccompanied minors. Unaccompanied minors seeking asylum in Hungary (UAMAS) and UAMs enjoying international protection, as well as UAMs not seeking asylum are now placed in child protection facilities in Fót and Hódmezvásárhely, respectively	EMN report  p.13/factsheet p.1	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
