2881	Hungary	Common European Asylum System	2015	Act CXL of 2015 - provides for the establishment of transit zones at the borders where asylum-seekers are temporarily accommodated for the purpose of immigration and refugee status determination: - During the procedure conducted at the border, the applicant is neither entitled to stay/obtain a permit authorising stay in the territory of Hungary, nor does she or he have the right to work in a reception centre or at a workplace - Asylum seekers can be held in the transit zone for a period of maximum 4 weeks. - The refugee authority shall deliver a decision on admissibility with priority but no later than within 8 days. - The deadline for submitting a judicial review request was extended from 3 days to 7 days.  - the border procedure cannot be applied to vulnerable individuals requiring special treatment, in practice, there is no assessment mechanism in place, only visible vulnerabilities are considered.	EMN	Mid-level change	National policy	Border and land control	Surveillance technology/control powers	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
