2999	Iceland	expulsion rules reiterated	2003	Act on Foreigners 96/2002 entered into force January 1st, 2003, replacing the 1965 Act - reiterates the rules for expulsion of a foreigner if he is living illegally in Iceland; if he has been sentenced in Iceland or if a court has ordered that he shall be subjected to security measures in consequence of conduct that can result in imprisonment for more than three months, or if he has been sentenced to imprisonment more than once in the previous three years; or if this is necessary with a view to national security or the public interest. >  Expulsion involves a prohibition against returning to Iceland later. The prohibition against returning may be permanent or limited in time, however generally not for a period shorter than three years.	http://eng.innanrikisraduneyti.is/laws-and-regulations/nr/105 [accessed on 20.02.2014]	Minor change	National policy	Exit	Expulsion	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	No change		
