3275	Ireland	new information system to track refused and admitted foreigners	2003	Roll out of the GNIB (Garda National Immigration Bureau) Information system to all ports of entry  completed in the first quarter of 2003 - Data, including photographs, are held on all persons who have been refused leave to land, all those who are the subject of deportation orders and almost all legally resident non-EEA nationals.  > The Certificate of Registration (residence permit) issued to all third country nationals who reside in Ireland for a period longer than three months now incorporates smart card technology whereby a microchip containing the persons photograph and registration details is included.	Quinn and Hughes 2005: 16	Major change	National policy	Border and land control	Surveillance technology/control powers	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
