3277	Ireland	programme to support irish diaspora created	2003	Establishment of the Support to Emigrant Groups Programme - providing grants to voluntary organisations that support Irish communities abroad. > The primary emphasis of funding has been, and continues to be, supporting frontline information and welfare services for vulnerable Irish emigrants. Total expenditure under the Programme totalled 11.8m in 2006, with a total of 184 groups receiving grants. This represents an almost fourfold increase in funding since 2003, when 73 groups received 3.1m in funding.	https://www.dfa.ie/media/dfa/alldfawebsitemedia/newspress/publications/2007-vfm-policy-review-of-irish-emigrant-groups-programme.pdf [accessed on 14.01.2014]	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to social benefits and socio-economic rights	Diaspora	Citizens	N/A	Less restrictive		
