3279	Ireland	unit to deal with diaspora of irish abroad	2004	Establishment of the 'Irish Abroad Unit' within the Ministry of foreign affairs > This unit was established as a result of the 2002 policy document, 'Ireland and the Irish Abroad' with ongoing commitment to emgirant welfare but new priorities of promoting links with the Irish diaspora particularly around culture and heritage. The Irish Abroad Unit operates the Support to Emigrant Groups Programme under which grants are provided to voluntary organisations that support Irish communities abroad.	https://www.dfa.ie/media/dfa/alldfawebsitemedia/newspress/publications/2007-vfm-policy-review-of-irish-emigrant-groups-programme.pdf [accessed on 14.01.2014]	Minor change	National policy	Integration	Institutional capacities	Diaspora	Citizens	N/A	Less restrictive		
