3332	Ireland	visa waiver programme for tourists of some countries	2011	In June 2011 the first Irish Short-Stay Visa Waiver Programme - to increase tourism. The waiver allows travel to Ireland on a valid UK visa for tourists, business persons and long-term residents who have lawfully entered the United Kingdom. The programme was announced as a pilot and extended for  four years in March 2012. > Nationals of sixteen emerging economies are included under the Programme including, China, certain Gulf States, India, the Russian Federation, Belarus, Ukraine and Turkey.	SOPEMI 2012: 238	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Travel visa/permit	All	Specific nationalities	16 emerging economies	Less restrictive		
