3491	Italy	Regularisation of irregular workers	1998	Fourth regularisation programme for foreigners in irregular situations (following those of 1986, 1990 and 1996) - lasted until October 1999  > A series of decrees followed in which the government regularized groups of unauthorized immigrants who had been present on Italian soil prior to March 27 1998, had housing, and whose employers paid taxes on their wages. An Interior Ministry circular dated 13 May 1999 has further relaxed the regularisation procedure so that more persons may benefit. The most important provision of the ministerial circular is the possibility of a deadline extension until 20 October 1999 for persons as yet unable to submit all the papers required. In order to make things easier for self-employed workers, the circular also stipulates that persons unable to prove that their annual income is at least equal to the benchmark minimum for Italy may submit their applications for regularisation with an undertaking to supply all the necessary details of income when the permits come up for first renewal, i.e. in one years time. Finally, the circular broadens the range of acceptable proof of presence in Italy prior to 28 March 1998.	SOPEMI 1999: 163; COMPAS 2005: 3	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Regularisation	Irregular migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
