3565	Italy	stricter family reunification conditions	2008	Legislative Decree no. 160 (October 3rd, 2008) - restricts the right to family reunification for legal age spouses who are not legally separated, minors who are not married (with the prior consent of the parent), for legal age dependent children (only if totally disabled), and for dependent parents (aged 65 and over and if the other children are unable to support them for serious health reasons). > Concerning income requirements, the decree stipulates that for each family member one must have an available income equal to half (and not less) the annual amount provided by annual social assistance, plus half the amount for each family member. As for the reunification of two or more children under the age of 14, or of two or more family members of persons under subsidiary protection, one will need an income of not less than twice the amount of annual social assistance. As well, a mandatory health insurance or registration at the National Health Services is required for parents who are 65 or over.	EMN 2008: 16	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Family members	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
