3597	Italy	Popular initiative to ease naturalisation requirements	2012	2012 popular initiative was presented to amend Law no. 91 of February 1992 on new rules on citizenship (A.C. 5030) - aiming at revising the current Italian legislation, with particular reference to the second generations and long-term residents. It was supported by 100,000 signatures and was assigned to the Constitutional Affairs Committee of the Chamber of Deputies. The proposal was similar to others previously submitted and joined in the debate on new rules which should facilitate the acquisition of Italian citizenship by correlating the principle of ius soli with the requirement of regularity of stay for at least one year by one of the parents  regardless of his/her formal residence, which is often hampered by the Registry Office rules. In addition, among other measures, the popular initiative law foresees for the minor who has attended a primary or secondary course of education, or an educational or vocational training, the possibility of acquiring citizenship at request of the parent. For adults, however, due to bureaucracy and red tape, there is a proposal of reduction from 10 to 5 years of the time needed to submit an application for citizenship on the basis of long-term residence.	EMN 2012: 13	N/A	N/A	Integration	Access to citizenship	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
