4183	Luxembourg	special education support for children of immigrants	1991	Since 1991 the Ministry of National Education has been dedveloping a general approach aimed at promoting the integration of children of immigrant on the basis of their special needs, in particular language constraints.  > The objective is one school for all, but with special measures for foreigners with particular difficulties. The trilingual basis of education -Luxembourgish, French, German- remains as before, but special arrangements apply to foreign children  so they are not handicapped by their lack of familiarity with these languages at the outset. Foreign pupils are to be integrated into Luxembourg schools with due regard to their native culture and mother tongue. Measures to apply these principles include additional tuition, preschool education and the development of reception classes, as well as equal opportunity measures in employment, housing and health care.	SOPEMI 1995: 104; SOPEMI 2003a: 216	Mid-level change	National policy	Integration	Language, housing and cultural integration programmes	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
