4332	Luxembourg	Integration	2016	Test phase for a plurilingual education in nurseries (children aged 1-4) undertaken in eight nurseries from March to December 2016 - the programme aims to stimulate language development and communication skills, provide early individualised exposure to French and Luxembourgish and thereby enhance local integration	EMN  p.41	Minor change	National policy	Integration	Language, housing and cultural integration programmes	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
4333	Luxembourg	Integration, youth and children	2016	Answer of the Minister of National Education, Childhood and Youth to parliamentary question n°2070 - the age bracket of the pupils cared for by the CASNA (Reception desk for newly arrived pupils) was broadened from 12-17 years to 12-24 years  - Development of a pilot project to provide youngsters welcomed by CASNA with apprenticeships in high-tech professions in the English language	EMN  p.43 , p.44	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Integration	Access to social benefits and socio-economic rights	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
4334	Luxembourg	Centre for Integration and Social Cohesion	2016	Inauguration of the Luxembourgish Centre for Integration and Social Cohesion (LISKO) on 13 June 2016  aims to 1) Empower refugees and increase their autonomy by providing personalised support based on intercultural understanding and translation if needed and to 2) Insert refugees in local integrative measures by establishing links to social services and associations	EMN  p.34	Minor change	National policy	Integration	Institutional capacities	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
4335	Luxembourg	Agreements, ransfer of workers temporary assignments	2016	Laws of 5 April 2016 and 29 November 2016 approving the Convention on Social Security between the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg and the Republic of Albania and the Phillipines respectively - the agreements aim at preventing double coverage of social security contributions for temporary assignments in the other country by exempting transferred workers from the obligation to contribute to the social security system of the other state where they are temporarily working for a maximum of 24months, as long as they have obtained a Certificate of Coverage (CoC)	https://home.kpmg/xx/en/home/insights/2016/07/flash-alert-2016-075.html	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Specific categories	Specific nationalities	Albania and  Phillipines	Less restrictive		
