4379	Luxembourg	International Protection including Asylum	2018	Law of 18 July 2018 amending the Asylum Act  allows the Director of the OLAI (or his delegate) to request the assistance of the Grand Ducal Police when an AIP objects in a violent or threatening manner to the execution of transfer to another facility	EMN	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Institutional capacities	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
4380	Luxembourg	UAM	2018	Law of 20 July 2018 approving the Council of Europe Convention on preventing and combating violence against women and domestic violence (known as the 'Istanbul Convention') - punishes anyone who practices, facilitates or promotes any form of genital mutilation of a female person, with or without the consent of the female, with three to five years imprisonment and a fine of 500 to 10,000 (imprisonment and fines increase if genital mutilation results in additional harm (incurable illness) or even death and if done to a minor)	EMN  p.49	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Other sanctions	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
4381	Luxembourg	National Action Plan on Integration	2018	Adoption of the National Action Plan on Integration (Integration NAP) on 13 July 2018  the plan provides an overall framework for the national integration policy and focuses on two fields of action, namely the reception and social follow-up of applicants for international protection and the integration of all non-Luxembourgish nationals residing in Luxembourg  These two domains were completed by three transversal domains: access to information and interaction, the quality of services as well as national and international cooperation and coordination. The fight against discrimination and the promotion of diversity and equal opportunities were an integral part of the multiannual integration plan	EMN  factsheet p.2	Mid-level change	National policy	Integration	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
4382	Luxembourg	Mediation service, integration	2018	Law of 18 June 2018  creates a mediation service for educational continuity, inclusion and integration as part of the ministry of Education's central structures.The mediation service addresses individual complaints from pupils and their representatives as well as school staff, with a view to providing the best possible and pragmatic solutions and thus maintaining the learners in education. In particular, it examines if the existing resources have been properly applied, respectively if the system can be improved.	https://eacea.ec.europa.eu/national-policies/eurydice/content/national-reforms-school-education-40_en	Mid-level change	National policy	Integration	Institutional capacities	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
