4528	Malta	L.N. 288 of 2015  introduced a Golden Visa programme	2015	L.N. 288 of 2015  introduced a Golden Visa programme which aimed to attract non-EU/EEA nationals who, with their registered dependants, are entitled to a certificate deemed to be a residence permit allowing the beneficiaries to reside, settle or stay indefinitely in Malta - The main applicant must commit to pay a contribution of EUR30,000 and must prove self-sufficiency via an annual income of at least EUR100,000 arising outside Malta, or capital of at least EUR500,000	https://uk.practicallaw.thomsonreuters.com/9-627-9039?transitionType=Default&contextData=(sc.Default)&firstPage=true	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Family members	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
4529	Malta	Strategy for the Reception of Asylum Seekers and Irregular Migrants	2015	Publishing of the Strategy for the Reception of Asylum Seekers and Irregular Migrantsin December 2015  introduced the concept of Initial Reception Centres as well as Open Reception Centres and regulated detention and alternatives to detention, financial and social support, access to the labour market and access to medical care Changes in practice regarding unaccompanied minors (UAMs)  they were not detained but rather placed in Initial Reception Centre (for max 10 days) waiting for medical clearance and age assessment	EMN 2015 factsheet p.1	N/A	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
