4537	Malta	new age assessment procedure	2017	Establishment of a new age assessment procedure   The new procedure is divided into three phases, consisting of a preliminary age assessment undertaken by a social worker; a full age assessment (when the social workers assessment is inconclusive); and the issuing of a decision on whether a care order is needed (if the person is found to be a minor)	EMN 2017 factsheet p.2	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Institutional capacities	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
