4776	Netherlands	Common European Asylum System, accelerated procedure	2014	Introduction of an accelerated procedure for repeated applications on 1 January 2014 approximately 2 weeks after receiving the application the IND schedules an appointment where the applicant puts forward new elements to consider and a decision is made within three days.  If the application requires further investigation, it will be dealt under the general or extended procedure.	EMN  p.30	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
