4778	Netherlands	Common European Asylum System, screening aims to check whether there is an actual relationship between adult(s) and presumed children	2014	Introduction of a screening of asylum applications of families with minor children at external borders on 1 September 2014 - the screening aims to check whether there is an actual relationship between adult(s) and presumed children, and whether there are well-founded reasons to refuse entry into the Netherlands (e.g., suspicion of war crimes).  - If the outcome of the screening shows that there is no cause for further investigation, then the family may travel to a reception centre to proceed with the asylum procedure. - If further investigation is required the family is placed in the new closed family care facility in Zeist. That is where the family also proceeds with the asylum procedure.  - If it is suspected that the adult(s) and children are not related, then the adult will be placed in border detention and the child will be placed under supervision of the guardianship organisation Nidos.	EMN  p.28	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
