4800	Netherlands	Common European Asylum System, Border	2015	Implementation of the European Reception and Procedures Directives on 20 July 2015  restructures the former procedure at the border as a border procedure within the meaning of the directive. The decision on refusal or entry to the Netherlands is suspended for a maximum of 4 weeks and the asylum seeker stays in detention at the external EU border (at Schiphol airport). During this period, the IND may reject the claim as: Not considered due to the application of the Dublin Regulation, Inadmissible or Manifestly unfounded. If the examination takes longer than 4 weeks or another ground of rejection is applicable, the detention measure is lifted, the asylum seeker is allowed to enter the Netherlands and the treatment of the application is continued in the regular procedure.	https://asylumineurope.org/reports/country/netherlands/asylum-procedure/procedures/border-procedure-border-and-transit-zones/	Minor change	National policy	Border and land control	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
