4830	Netherlands	Asylum procedure, multi-track policy, safe country of oigin	2016	Introduction of the multi-track policy on 1 March 2016  consists of five tracks that provide different procedures (tracks) for different target groups during the asylum procedure  - Track 1 (Dublin) and 4(General Asylum Procedure) have remained the same. Track 2 (Safe country of origin or legal stay in another EU Member State) is introduced and Tracks 3 (Evident decisions to grant an application) and 5 (Evident decision to grant an application after brief investigation) have yet to become active. The purpose of the multitrack policy is to prevent the waiting times for asylum seekers, which rose significantly in 2015 due to the high influx, from dragging on further and to structure the asylum procedure as efficiently as possible.	EMN  p.36/37	major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
