4845	Netherlands	Return and readmission	2016	On 8th April, the Council of State ruled that a repeat asylum application by a third-country national no longer automatically leads to a cancellation of a previously issued return decision. During the asylum process, the return procedure is suspended, and reinstated if the asylum application is rejected. This ruling is meant to make returns more effective, as a return decision no longer has to be taken anew each time.  Given the higher influx of third-country nationals from safe countries of origin, foreigners from Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kosovo, Macedonia, Montenegro, Serbia, Morocco and Algeria will no longer receive return support. However, an aeroplane ticket is still offered to those who return voluntarily.	EMN	Mid-level change	National policy	Exit	Reintegration/return programmes	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
