4986	Norway	permit for skilled migrants consolidated	2010	New Immigration Act of 15 May 2008 entered into force on 1 January 2010 - replacing the previously separate work and residence permit by a single residence permit, which generally also entitles work permission. Among the five main categories of labour immigrants, the Immigration Act lists Skilled workers (those with education level corresponding at least to vocational training at the level of Norwegian upper secondary education, or with corresponding vocational education.) They are entitled to family reunion and offered opportunities for permanent residence.	SOPEMI 2010: 230; EMN 2011: 16	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	No change		
