5000	Norway	Integration Report	2011	Report Better Integration  Goals, Strategies, Measures published in 2011 - finds that immigrants in Norway are better integrated into the labour market than the OECD average, although labour market participation is lower for immigrants than for ethnic Norwegians. Immigrants more frequently live in relative poverty, and social mobility may be more limited. The Committee recommends that the focus of integration efforts be shifted from providing equal opportunities toward assuring equal results. The Committee also recommends several broad and long-term strategies to increase the labour market participation of immigrants, with focus on immigrant women. Further, it recommends the extension of programs providing free classes in Norwegian language and social studies.	SOPEMI 2012: 258; EMN 2011: 21	N/A	N/A	Integration	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
