5172	Poland	Polish ethnicity card grants right to enter, stay and work	2007	Act on the Polish Ethnicity Card was passed in September 2007 - The document entitles the holder to take up any legal occupation without a work permit and also function as an entry visa, facilitating frequent border crossings. It is valid for ten years and may be extended. > Ethnic Poles originating from states of the former Soviet Union (Belarus, Estonia, Lithuania, the Republic of Moldova, the (entire) Russian Federation and Ukraine) are eligible.  In order to acquire the Karta applicants have to prove that they are of Polish descent, have basic Polish language skills, and that they have cultivated an attachment to Poland and Polish culture. Unlike a visa issued under the Repatriation Act, the Karta Polaka will not entitle its holder to settle in Poland, nor will the holder acquire Polish citizenship.	SOPEMI 2008: 280; Focus Migration 2008: 3	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Diaspora	Specific nationalities	Ethnic Poles in Former Soviet Union	Less restrictive		
