5184	Poland	campain to incite return of polish diaspora	2008	In November 2008, Prime Minister Donald Tusk started a government campaign entitled 'Have you got a Plan to return?' - aiming to facilitate smooth returns and showcase employment opportunities for the Polish diaspora. > The campaign includes a guide book and a website for those who have decided to return. These include practical information about necessary paperwork, answers to problems return migrants have to face, and opportunities in the local labor market with lists of local employment agencies and job openings in areas where return migrants might like to settle.  The government has spent about 4 million Polish zloty (about 1 million euros) on the campaign.	MPI 2010	Minor change	National policy	Integration	Reintegration/return programmes	Diaspora	All	N/A	Less restrictive		
