5193	Poland	agreement with Ukraine creates special permit for border area residents	2009	The bilateral agreement on local border traffic between Poland and Ukraine was implemented on January 1 2009 - creating a specific permit for residents of the border areas to allow them to regularly cross the border and stay in the area for a maximum of 60 days each time.  > Residents who live near the Poland-Ukraine border can now pay 20 euros and receive a special permit, valid for two years (and extendable to five years), that allows them to cross the border, travel within 30 kilometers (19 miles) of the border, and stay no more than three months in any half-year period.	SOPEMI 2009; MPI 2010	Mid-level change	Multi- or bilateral policy	Legal entry and stay	Travel visa/permit	All	Specific nationalities	Ukraine	Less restrictive		
