5203	Poland	EU blue card implemented	2012	In April 2012, the Foreigners Act and the Act on Promotion of Employment and Labour Market Institutions were amended - transposing the EU Highly Qualified Directive creating an EU Blue Card permit.	SOPEMI 2013: 284	Mid-level change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Work visa/permit	Skilled/high-skilled workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
5204	Poland	first draft of new Aliens Act	2012	A first draft of a new Act on Aliens was presented in October 2012 with the goal of entering into force in the first half of 2013 - The law does not propose fundamental changes in the status of foreigners, although a rigid legislative approach would require subsequent changes to be made through amendments.	SOPEMI 2013: 284	N/A	N/A	Legal entry and stay	Contextual elements	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
5205	Poland	new naturalisastion route possible for integrated people	2012	2009 Citizenship Act entered into force in August 2012 (it was passed in Parliament in 2009) -  opens a new route to naturalisation by the Voivod (Article 30) to 1) those who have resided uninterruptedly and legally on Polish territory for at least ten years, are in possession (at the moment of application) of one of three types of permanent residence permit, who have a stable and regular income and a legal title to habitable premises, and who know the Polish language; 2) those who have resided uninterruptedly on Polish territory for at least three years on the basis of one of three types of permanent residence permit, who have a stable and regular income and a legal title to habitable premises, and who know the Polish language; 3) those who have resided uninterruptedly on Polish territory for at least two years on the basis of one of three types of permanent residence permit, who have been married to a Polish citizen for at least three years, and who know the Polish language; 4) those who have resided uninterruptedly on Polish territory for at least two years on the basis of one of three types of permanent residence permit and who are stateless, and who know the Polish language and 5) those who have resided uninterruptedly on Polish territory for at least two years on the basis of a residence permit that was acquired in connection with refugee status granted in Poland and who know the Polish language  > In this way a legal entitlement to citizenship is created for some categories of foreigners.	Gorny and Pudzianowska 2013: 11	Minor change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
5206	Poland	restoring citizenship to those denaturalized in the past	2012	2009 Citizenship Act entered into force in August 2012 (it was passed in Parliament in 2009) - introduced a new mode of acquiring Polish citizenship through restitution: restitution of Polish citizenship on application is possible if a foreigner lost Polish citizenship before 1 January 1999 on the basis of regulations in three acts on Polish citizenship of 1920, 1951, and 1962.  > It is too early to see any trends in the statistics on the numbers of people acquiring citizenship under the new legislation.	Gorny and Pudzianowska 2013: 12	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	Diaspora	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
