5291	Portugal	Diaspora strategy	1990	The XVth Portuguese Government has defined the Programme concerning Portuguese communities abroad  > Six main objectives: 1) to maintain and promote the Portuguese language and culture; 2) to provide these communities with fuller and more up-to-date information; 3) to create an awareness  among descendents of these communities of the values, cultures and econonmic potential of Portugal; 4) to defend the rights and interests of Portuguese living abroad; 5) to promote and uphold the exercise of political rights both in Portugal and in the host countries; 6) to create favorable conditions for the resettlement of Portuguese who decide to return to Portugal for good.	SOPEMI 1991: 62	N/A	N/A	Integration	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	Diaspora	Citizens	N/A	N/A		
5292	Portugal	vocational training for diaspora created	1990	Measures regarding Portuguese citizens abroad were organised from 1990 onwards - vocational training courses covering a number of different areas such as management, accountancy and skilled trades were organised in France, Belgium, Germany, Luxembourg and the Netherlands. > Background: Most of the adult Portuguese living within the European Community do not possess sufficient occupational skills and, generally speaking, relatively few of them attend vocational training courses in their host country. In an effort to remedy this, the Portuguese authorities have set themselves the following aims: 1. To reduce unempolyment among adult emigrants; 2. To facilitate their geographical and occupational mobility; 3. To ease the re-enry of voluntary returnees into the Portuguese labour market.	SOPEMI 1992: 76	Major change	National policy	Integration	Language, housing and cultural integration programmes	Diaspora	Citizens	N/A	Less restrictive		
