5303	Portugal	new directorate for portuguese community abroad	1994	March 1994 creation of the New General Directorate for the Portuguese communities abroad > Across the world there are about 2000 associations of Portuguese residents abroad who directly elect deputies to the Parliament in Lisbon. The aim of emigration policy is to maintain links with emigrant communities abroad and to assist, and even encourage, the emigrant's return home. Measures are designed to safeguard and disseminate the Portuguese language, to provide links between the communities, to defend the interests and rights of Portuguese migrants and create conditions to make return to Portugal easier. To this end, two approaches have been developed. The first, for Portuguese nationals residing abroad, includes assitance for the teaching of Portuguese, grants to associations, missions and other agencies working with foreign resident Portuguese, the organisation of sociocultural exchanges and vocational training. The other measures, for Portuguese returning home, are designed to assist reintegration through financial assistance to learn Portuguese, vocational training, legal, economic and social services, special bank accounts and preferential credit through an emigrant savings scheme which makes capital loans.	SOPEMI 1995: 116	Major change	National policy	Integration	Institutional capacities	Diaspora	Citizens	N/A	Less restrictive		
