5385	Portugal	new quota system introduced	2007	Law 23/2007 of 4 July on the Entry, Stay, Departure and Expulsion of Foreigners - replaced the former quota system that governed the admission of labour migrants  by a so-called global contingent based on annual estimates of labour market needs that cannot be filled by the domestic labour market (including by other EU nationals).  > The Institute for Employment and Vocational Training (IEFP) will advertise, using an internet database in conjunction with the Portuguese consulates network, the labour shortages reported by Portuguese employers that cannot be met by the domestic labour market. Foreign workers interested in these offers are expected to contact the employer and to obtain either a work contract, the promise of a work contract or a personal and explicit manifestation of interest in her/his recruitment and can subsequently apply for a residence visa at a Portuguese embassy or consulate.	SOPEMI 2008:272; EMN 2009: 33	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Quota/target	All migrant workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
