5388	Portugal	First Integration Plan	2007	May 2007  Plan for Integration of Immigrants - seeks to provide an overall, integrated and comprehensive solution, which systematises the States objectives and commitments while hosting and integrating immigrants who have come to Portugal.  > To this end, it identified a set of 122 measures, reflected in 295 goals distributed over 20 sectorial and transversal areas, whose primary purpose is to receive and fully integrate immigrants, keeping in mind not just the economic and social aspects but also equally important issues concerning cultural and religious diversity, citizenship, participation and rights. The plan was evaluated two years after it was implemented and the results were published in the 2nd PII Implementation Report which shows that 81% of its measures have already been implemented or are being implemented.	SOPEMI 2008:272; EMN 2009: 46; EMN 2006: 17	N/A	N/A	Integration	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
