5400	Portugal	lowering of means of subsistence requirement for all permits	2009	Ordinance No. 760/2009 of 16 June - adopts exceptional measures with regard to the means of subsistence that foreign citizens must possess to be able to stay in the national territory, reducing them in the context of the international economic crisis > The means of subsistence necessary for third country nationals to obtain a Residence Permit were reduced in 2009 considering the impact of the current international economic crisis on immigrants who live and work in Portuguese territory, particularly with regard to situations of unemployment or professional instability. The ordinance stipulates that On an exceptional basis, for applicants who can prove that they are in a situation of involuntary unemployment and declare that they cannot maintain the availability or the possibility of legally acquiring the means of subsistence required, the period of stay corresponding to the type of visa can be prorogued. This exceptional regime has also been extended to include the members of the applicants respective family unit, including in situations in which a family reunification took place. The criterion for determining the means of subsistence is, for the first adult, 50% of the Minimum Monthly Guaranteed Wage and 30% for the other members of the family unit.	EMN 2009: 36	Minor change	National policy	Integration	Entry visa/stay permit	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
5401	Portugal	Second Integration Plan	2010	Approval of the II Immigrant Integration Plan (2010-2013) - which embodies the States commitments with regard to the integration of immigrants, namely in the areas of culture, language, employment, professional training and housing. > This plan comprised 90 measures including steps aimed at promoting the fight against scholastic abandonment and failure by the descendants of immigrants; a reinforcement of professional training for immigrant communities; an emphasis on intensifying programmes aimed at teaching the Portuguese language and tools to facilitate access by immigrants to fully exercise their individual and social rights, namely in the areas of health, housing and justice. Two new areas of intervention also stand out: the promotion of diversity and intercultural relations and elderly immigrants.	EMN 2010: 3, 22	N/A	N/A	Integration	Action Plan, Strategy, Report	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
