5725	Slovakia	financial requirement introduced for entry	1995	Act no. 73/1995 concerning foreigners residence status came into force and replaced the 1992 act -required foreign migrants to show that they have the means to support themselves during their stay. > This was done in response to the growing number of persons crossing Slovak borders (90 million in 1995 compared with 41 million in 1993) Upon request, the person applying for visa and/or different type of stay (short-term (up to 180 days), long-term stay (up to 1 year, with possibility to renew the stay each time for another year) or permanent residence must give the proof of sufficient finance, accomodation, clean criminal record and health record (no contagious or terminal illness).	SOPEMI 1998: 162	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
