5731	Slovakia	increase in bilateral treaties on labour exchange	1996	Bilateral agreements have been signed with Hungary, Germany, Poland, Russia and Vietnam and are presently being negotiated with Austria, Switzerland, Ukraine, Romania and Hungary. Many of the agreements set quotas and objectives or restrictions ( e.g. skill development, language training or sector of employment) and are based on the principle of reciprocity which means that flows are two ways (the only unilateral agreement is with Vietnam), with Slovak workers also migrating temporarily for work to the other country. Workers entering the Slovak Republic through these agreements also need a residence permit. These bilateral agreements provide for the reciprocal hosting of a fixed number of workers for a limited period.	SOPEMI 1997: 153; SOPEMI 1999: 203	N/A	Multi- or bilateral policy	Legal entry and stay	Recruitment/assisted migration programmes	All migrant workers	Specific nationalities	Those with bilateral treaties	N/A		
