5964	Slovenia	naturalisation of previously permanent residents facilitated	1994	1994 Amendment to the 1991 citizenship law - addressed the problem of the 'erased' residents in two ways: Art. 39a stipulates that a person is considered a Slovenian citizen if he or she was registered as a permanent resident on 23 December 1990 and has permanently and actually lived in Slovenia since that date. On the other hand, according to the new art.41, persons younger than 23 and older than eighteen years who were born in Slovenia can declare themselves Slovenian citizens if one of their parents was a citizen of Slovenia at the time of their birth, but the parents later agreed on adopting the citizenship of another republic	Medved 2013: 8	Mid-level change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	All	Specific nationalities	Former Yugoslavian countries	Less restrictive		
