6012	Slovenia	quota for newly issued work permits introduced	2004	In 2004, Slovenia adopted an overall quota for the annual issuance of new work permits for immigrants from outside of the European Economic Area - The quota has been set at a maximum of 5% of the active population. > Within this overall framework, annual numerical limits are fixed depending on the economic situation.  Background: In the 1993-2004 period, the number of employed aliens who could work on the basis of work permits varied between 35 and 40 thousand. It was expected that after Slovenias 2004 accession to the EU, the number of migrant workers would steadily rise.	SOPEMI 2011: 320; EMN 2007: 11	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Quota/target	All migrant workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
