6020	Slovenia	quasi citizenship regime created for slovenian minorities abroad	2006	2006 Act Regulating Relations between the Republic of Slovenia and Slovenians Abroad -  introduced an external quasi citizenship that grant special privileges to co-ethnic minorities in neighbouring countries and Slovene emigrants and workers abroad who do not possess formal Slovenian citizenship. > Aiming at maintaining and developing the Slovene language and culture, preserving cultural heritage and national identity among Slovenians abroad, this legislation facilitates and promotes the integration of Slovenians abroad into the social and political life of the mother nation.  Acquisition of this status which is a novelty in the Slovenian legal order would primarily depend on descent, activity in Slovenian organisations abroad and active ties with the homeland. When in Slovenia, the holders of this status will enjoy preferential enrolment at institutions of higher education, equal access to research projects and public cultural goods, such as libraries or archives, as well as equal property rights. They will also enjoy priority in employment over other third-country nationals.	Medved 2013: 17, 18	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to social benefits and socio-economic rights	Diaspora	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
