6028	Slovenia	integration programme for all migrants created	2008	Decree on the integration of aliens entered into force on 15 July 2008 - determines methods and conditions for the inclusion of aliens who have a permit for residence in the Republic of Slovenia, in the cultural, economic and social life of the Republic of Slovenia. > Since then, there are several integration programs implemented by the Ministry of Interior, Employment Service and NGOs, such as Slovenian language courses for foreigners, learning Slovenian culture and history, Info Point for Foreigners, website Information for Foreigners (in Slovenian and six foreign languages)	EMN 2008: 13; http://www.migrationonline.cz/en/an-overview-of-the-migration-policies-and-trends-slovenia [accessed on 14.01.2014]	Major change	National policy	Integration	Language, housing and cultural integration programmes	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
6029	Slovenia	new conditions for getting a visa introduced	2008	2008 Amendment to the Aliens Act - introduced new conditions for the issuing of a visa > A guarantor is a natural or legal person who provides surety for an alien during the period of their residence in the Republic of Slovenia, with a letter of guarantee. An alien, in the procedure of issue of a visa, demonstrates with the letter of guarantee the purpose of residence, accommodation and means of subsistence in the Republic of Slovenia and for return to the country of origin. In addition, guaranteed travel health insurance and more clearly defined means of subsistence were laid down, which an alien similarly must have who is applying for the issue of a visa.	EMN 2008: 12	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Entry visa/stay permit	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	More restrictive		
