6052	Slovenia	quota for work permits now optional instrument	2011	2011 Amendment of the Law on Employment and Work of Foreigners - stipulates that the government is not obliged to define a yearly quota. It is now only an optional instrument which the government can use any time, depending on the actual situation on the labour market in Slovenia.  > In 2011 and 2012, instead of defining a yearly quota, the government stick to another provision of the above mentioned law, stipulating that employment of third country nationals is allowed only if there are no suitable unemployed Slovenian or EU citizens available for that kind of job.	http://www.migrationonline.cz/en/an-overview-of-the-migration-policies-and-trends-slovenia [accessed on 14.01.2014]	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Quota/target	All migrant workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Change in restrictiveness cannot be assessed		
