6279	Spain	no visa for latin american visitors	1991	No visa requirement for Latin American visitors introduced > Even though the visa to Maghreb citizens has been introduced in order to conform the 'European community norms' there is no visa requirement for Latin Americans of Hispanic origin who, under the terms of the 1863 Treaty of Peace and Friendship between Spain and its former colonies, have the right to live and work in Spain under the same terms and conditions as Spanish nationals.	SOPEMI 1992: 77	Fine-tuning change	Multi- or bilateral policy	Legal entry and stay	Free mobility rights/agreements	All migrants	Specific nationalities	Latin Americans of Hispanic origin	No change		
6280	Spain	Creation of Migration Directorate	1991	The Directorate General for Migration was set up on 4 October within the Ministry of Labour and Social Security, taking over from the Spanish Insitute for Emigration  > The new Directorate for Migration replaces the Spanish Institute for Emigration and it is responsible for planning and implementing projects for emigrants, assisting internal migration, planning migratory flows and controlling the issue and renewal of work permits.	SOPEMI 1992: 77	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Institutional capacities	All migrants	All	N/A	Change in restrictiveness cannot be assessed		
