6284	Spain	Creation of Interministerial Commission for Foreigners	1992	Establishment of an Interministerial Commission for Foreigners in May 1992 > This body co-ordinates the activities of the ministries concerned and formulates general policy principles for the treatment of foreigners to be considered by the government. The Interministerial Comission has 4 sub committees: one covering visas and international co-operation, another covering general conditions for foreigners, a third for employment and migrant flows and a fourth for th eadvancement and integration of immigrants and refugees.	SOPEMI 1994: 93	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Institutional capacities	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Change in restrictiveness cannot be assessed		
