6341	Spain	new, more flexible quota system	2002	A new, flexible quota system introduced in December 2001 - with the total quota set at 10 884 stable work permits, and 21 195 temporary work permit authorisations for 2002.  > A process for consulting the social partners, with large-scale employer involvement, was introduced with effect from 2002 with the object of establishing quotas by sector, province and type of job, on the basis of the real needs of the labour market and taking account of both the local and national situations.  Quotas are established as follows: i) the employers organisations submit, at provincial level, their affiliated members labour demand which the latter believe cannot be met in their own labour market area during the coming year; ii) joint provincial committees reassess the request made in light of employment conditions at local level; iii) an executive committee of the Ministry for Employment and Solidarity rules on labour requirements at national level and has the Council of ministers approve the quotas; iv) the said quotas are then distributed to the employers organisations which are responsible for sharing them between their members; v) candidates are then selected in countries of origin via the relevant embassies.	SOPEMI 2003b: 270	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Quota/target	All migrant workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
