6344	Spain	recovery of Spanish citizenship facilitated	2003	Citizenship Act of 8 October 2002 (implemented on 9 January 2003) - makes it possible for all persons who had Spanish nationality at birth or who were children of Spanish parents at the time of their birth to be granted or to recover Spanish nationality.  > Every restriction of age when opting for Spanish citizenship for descendants of Spanish citizens born in Spain was removed, as well as the obligation of renouncing to their previous nationality.	SOPEMI 2003b: 269; Marin et al 2012: 14	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	Diaspora	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
6345	Spain	amendment of the new quota system	2003	Amendment of the quota system in January 2003 > Following the disappointing results of the introduction of a quota system (only 13 600 jobs, of which 3 100 were available under stable work permits, were filled out of the 32 000 job vacancies approved in December 2001), the government made a number of amendments to the relevant legislation in January 2003: i) firms wishing to employ more than five foreign workers are also entitled to publish job vacancies themselves; ii) employers can now rehire a worker who had temporarily returned to his home country, but the latter cannot be hired by another employer; iii) the government can reassign unfilled job vacancies to the provinces where demand is highest; iv) the administrative procedures have been streamlined; v) the unions now have a role to play in quota assignment.  A preliminary quota of 13 700 temporary job vacancies and 10 600 stable job vacancies has been set for 2003.	SOPEMI 2005: 270	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Quota/target	All migrant workers	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
