6371	Spain	return measures for diaspora	2006	2006 Law on the Statute of Spanish Citizenship Abroad (Estatuto de la ciudadanía española en el exterior) - created facilities to return to Spain (to the emigrants themselves, as well as to the two following generations) to the estimated one and a half million Spanish nationals settled abroad as a result of the emigration flows that marked Spanish society during most of the twentieth century.	Marin et al 2012: 15	Major change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Reintegration/return programmes	Diaspora	Citizens	N/A	Less restrictive		
6372	Spain	recovery of Spanish citizenship for descendants of exiled spaniards during franco regime	2007	2007 Law of Historical Memory - allowed to recover Spanish nationality by origin for all those who could prove that their parents or grandparents had fled Spain due to political reasons between 18 July 1936 and 31 December 1955. The time window to apply for this recognition of Spanish nationality was limited to an initial two year period (with an extension of one additional year decided by the Spanish government, so finally until December 2011). >  This was linked to the need for reparation of the wrongdoings of the Franco period and the elimination of the symbols of his regime. The law had a considerable echo in some Latin American countries in which it was euphemistically called Ley de Nietos (Grandchildrens Law).	Marin et al 2012: 16	Major change	National policy	Integration	Access to citizenship	Diaspora	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive		
