6994	Sweden	reintegration aid for failed asylum seekers raised	2008	The Swedish Government raised, as from the 1st of November 2008, the reintegration allowance by 50 per cent. > Those mainly eligible for the allowance are failed asylum seekers who opt for voluntary return and who are returning to countries with very limited preconditions for reintegration, for example Iraq, Somalia and Afghanistan. The new allowance amounts to 30,000 SEK per adult, 15,000 SEK per child and a maximum of 75,000 SEK (app. 7,000 Euro) per family.	EMN 2008: 3, 13	Fine-tuning change	National policy	Exit	Reintegration/return programmes	Refugees, asylum seekers and other vulnerable people	Specific nationalities	Iraq, Afghanistan, Somalia	Less restrictive		
