7350	Switzerland	further discussion on citizenship reform, restrictive stance	2013	In the spring plenary session 2013, the National Council debated the Federal Councils reform bill on citizenship - It did not follow the Federal Councils initial proposal on a number of points. Firstly, it did not agree with a reduction of the minimum residence requirement to eight years and suggested setting the federal residence requirement at ten years. Secondly, the National Council proposes to abolish the facilitated procedure for young adults that allowed counting the years of residence between ages of 10 and 20 double (Nationalrat 2013a, 2013b). In sum, the amendments introduced by the National Council would lead to a further tightening of the already tough Swiss citizenship regime. It remains to be seen whether the Council of States will align with the National Councils hard line or whether it will adopt a more liberal stance.	Achermann et al 2013: 11, 12	N/A	N/A	Integration	Access to citizenship	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	N/A		
