7635	United Kingdom	A technical change to the salary bands that inform the monthly quota of Tier 2 (General) visas	2019	Amendment of the immigration rules, in force since 29 March 2019  introduced a technical change to the salary bands that inform the monthly quota of Tier 2 (General) visas (Restricted Certificate of Sponsorship requests) > the Government removed the bands and instead awards one point for each £1,000 of gross annual salary. This means that compared to the past where a whole salary band of applications (for example £49,999 - £54,999) was rejected in case of oversubscription, because there was no fair way of being able to decide which to approve and which not to, more applications can now be awarded within a monthly allocation, reducing potential refusals.	https://www.osborneclarke.com/insights/uk-immigration-changes-march-2019/	Minor change	National policy	Legal entry and stay	Access to social benefits and socio-economic rights	All migrants	All foreign nationalities	N/A	Less restrictive	Prior to this change, when the quota was oversubscribed, a whole salary band of applications (for example £49,999 - £54,999) was rejected, resulting in a large number of rejections, as there was no fair way of being able to decide which to approve and which not to.	
